What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Tyre Inflators Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Tyre Inflators Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the tyre inflators market would exhibit a CAGR of 4.83% for the forecast period. Growth in the production of passenger vehicles especially in the emerging economies, shifting and improving economic conditions of certain economies around the globe, growing concerns related to the safety of driver and passengers and increased focus of the manufacturers on the adoption of durable and impact resistant materials are the major factors attributable to the growth of tyre inflators market. This signifies that, the global tyre inflators market would stand tall by USD 1,610.59 million by the year 2028.

From the name itself, it is clear that the tyre inflators are the machines that are used to pump up the tires with adequate amount of air. The major components of any tyre inflators are a piston, an air tank, and a gauge. Therefore, the tyre inflators provide and accurate and legible pressure and are available in the market in different sizes.

Growth in the demand for effective and convenient safety accessories or components has resulted in growth in the market value. Growth and expansion of automotive industry especially in the developing economies coupled with growth in the awareness about the availability of portable tyre inflators will also create lucrative growth opportunities for the market. Increasing tyre related regulations imposed by the government will also foster the market growth. Increased focus of the manufacturers on expanding manufacturing plants and undertaking more research and development activities will further carve the way for the growth of market.

However, high costs associated with tyre inflators will pose a major challenge to the market growth rate. Also, fluctuations in the prices of raw materials will hamper the market growth rate. Lack of awareness among the population in regards to the significance of the product will further restrict the scope of growth for the market.

